>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ian McKellen", "Viggo Mortensen", "Orlando Bloom", "Bernard Hill"], :people_indexes=>[["Viggo Mortensen", [[308]]], ["Orlando Bloom", [[313]]], ["Bernard Hill", [[284]]]]}, {:index=>2, :text=>"Aragorn again plays a pivotal part in the finale, attempting to take back a throne that is rightfully his, Mortensen excellently shows so much development of his character over the three films, always fighting the good fight while looking out for those who matter most, now in the midst of leading a rebellion against Mordor.", :clean_text=>"aragorn again plays a pivotal part in the finale attempting to take back a throne that is rightfully his mortensen excellently shows so much development of his character over the three films always fighting the good fight while looking out for those who matter most now in the midst of leading a rebellion against mordor.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>50}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Viggo Mortensen"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>3, :text=>"But the real journey still soldiers on with Frodo (Elijah Wood) as he edges ever closer to Mordor, but the ring continues to overburden him, alienating his only friend, Sam (Sean Astin), who can't seem to do right, he continuously warns his friend of the threat of Gollum (Andy Serkis), who has a more expansive role here, we see his humble beginnings as one of the river folk, with his eventual descent into madness well documented.", :clean_text=>"but the real journey still soldiers on with frodo elijah wood as he edges ever closer to mordor but the ring continues to overburden him alienating his only friend sam sean astin who can't seem to do right he continuously warns his friend of the threat of gollum andy serkis who has a more expansive role here we see his humble beginnings as one of the river folk with his eventual descent into madness well documented.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>15, :cast=>35}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Elijah Woo