hat role.", :clean_text=>"there might have been one or two casting decisions i might have questioned but by and large the cast was stellar a few so magnificently that it difficult now to see anyone else in that role.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:cast=>170}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>21, :text=>"When the film was first announced, much of the debate was over who would portray Gandalf, and I remember some people being upset that not only was Sean Connery (the early favorite) not cast but an openly gay actor in the role instead.", :clean_text=>"when the film was first announced much of the debate was over who would portray gandalf and i remember some people being upset that not only was sean connery the early favorite not cast but an openly gay actor in the role instead.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{:cast=>170}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ian McKellen"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>22, :text=>"But it is now almost impossible to imagine anyone but Ian McKellan in the role.", :clean_text=>"but it is now almost impossible to imagine anyone but ian mckellan in the role.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{:cast=>70}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>23, :text=>"So many smaller roles made the film work, like David Wenham as Faramir (seen only a couple of years ago in the role of \"Audrey\" in MOULIN ROUGE), or Ian Holm as Bilbo, or Sean Bean as Boromir, or Cate Blanchett as Galadriel.", :clean_text=>"so many smaller roles made the film work like david wenham as faramir seen only a couple of years ago in the role of audrey in moulin rouge or ian holm as bilbo or sean bean as boromir or cate blanchett as galadriel.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:cast=>70}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>["David Wenham", "Cate Blanchett", "Ian Holm", "Sean Bean"], :people_indexes=>[["David Wenham", [[47]]], ["Cate Blanchett", [[177]]], ["Ian Holm", [[130]]], ["Sean Bean", [[144]]]]}, {:index=>24, :text=>"The only weakness in the movie is one that probably couldn't be overcome (and one that Peter Jackson has acknowledged in interviews):  Sauron.", :clean_text=>"the only weakness in the movie is one that probably couldn't be overcome and one that peter jackson has acknowledged in interviews sauron.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Peter Jackson"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>25, :text=>"What can you do with a bad guy who is merely a giant flaming eyeball?", :clean_text=>"what can you do with a bad guy who is merely a giant flaming eyeball?", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>26, :text=>"Just not much potential to do much more than what they were able to do.Peter Jackson deserves a special academy award for serving as the creative force that turned THE LORD OF THE RINGS into one of the great experiences in the history of cinema.", :clean_text=>"just not much potential to do much more than what they were able to do.peter jackson deserves a special academy award for serving as the creative force that turned the lord of the rings into one of the great experiences in the history of cinema.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>8.0, :people_tags=>["Peter Jackson"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>27, :text=>"Most of all, he deserves enormous credit for making all the technology subservient to the story, and not the other way around.", :clean_text=>"most of all he deserves enormous credit for making all the technology subservient to the story and not the other way around.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Peter Jackson"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>28, :text=>"The great battle for Minas Tirith might have devolved into a mere showcase for stellar special effects, like many moments in the past two STAR WARS films have, but not once did he lose touch with the human element, not there or at any other point.", :clean_text=>"the great battle for minas tirith might have devolved into a mere showcase for stellar special effects like many moments in the past two star wars films have but not once did he lose touch with the human element not there or at any other point.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:editing=>70}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>["Peter Jackson"], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"With the release of The Return of the King, the magnificient journey begun over two years ago is now over, and that is a bit sad. I never read the books by Tolkien and was not all that interested about all the hype over the release of the Fellowship of the Ring. After I saw the first movie I became hooked. The Return of the King is probably the best of the three, although I really loved the Fellowship of the Ring.This movie refocuses on the importance of the hobbits,especially Sam and Frodo, after all it is up to them to destroy the ring thus defeating the dark lord Sauron and all his minions. By the way, Sean Astin's performance in this movie is superb. After I first saw the Fellowship of the Ring I realized why I became a sort of convert to these movies; they deal with themes that are more than relevant to the real world. Courage, sacrifice, fear, loyalty, betrayal, etc., are all part of what makes these movies so appealling. People can look at these movies and get out of it what they want or they interpret, but I can clearly see a lot of Christian symbolism in the characters and the themes I just mentioned.The epic struggle between good and evil comes to a stunning climax in this movie with some of the greatest battle scenes ever brought to film (especially at the siege of Minis Tirith) even though so much of it is computer generated. But remarkably this movie tugs at the heart strings as well. The actors truly gave it their all with real emotional performances. Though the ending may have been predictable even if you did not read the books, it still has quite an emotional ending. I realized that the fellowship was over, the story complete, and it was quite sad. These have been some of the greatest movies ever brought to film. When it's all over you realized how much you felt for the characters and how exciting the adventure had been. A movie that can do this is a great movie.Bottom line, it may be a while before we ever see anything like these movies again. We can thank the film's producer, a talented crew and a great cast for bringing us a great movie that has become rare in Hollywood these days. As an afterthought, I would have liked to have seen Christopher Lee's character brought to a conclusion. I've read where his scenes will probably be included in the DVD edition, but it should have been included in the theatrical release, but that's just my opinion. Any other minor complaints I may have don't really matter.", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[22, 23], :date=>" 2004 January 16", :title=>"It Will Not Disappoint", :username=>nil, :location=>nil, :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/The-Lord-Rings-Widescreen-Theatrical/product-reviews/B00005JKZY"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"With the release of The Return of the King, the magnificient journey begun over two years ago is now over, and that is a bit sad. I never read the books by Tolkien and was not all that interested about all the hype over the release of the Fellowship of the Ring.", :clean_text=>"with the release of the return of the king the magnificient journey begun over two years ago is now over and that is a bit sad i never read the books by tolkien and was not all that interested about all the hype over the release of the fellowship of the ring.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{:plot=>30}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"After I saw the first movie I became hooked.", :clean_text=>"after i saw the first movie i became hooked.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_in