xt_tags=>{:vision=>20}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"This is the best edition of GBU that I have seen so far. I do not agree with the reviewer that complained about the absence of grain due to DNR. For me it looked sufficiently grainy and I could not see any DNR artifacts (on a 1080p plasma screen). There is some minor problem with the film's sprocket hole registration, meaning that the picture is shifting slightly in steady shots. This can be attributed to the 40 year old film technology, but it could have been corrected during the restoration.The language and subtitle options are awesome, even the two audio commentaries, by Schickel and Frayling, have subtitles. I still have to take the time to enjoy the commentary by Frayling, which is new to this edition. The Schickel commentary was already on the 2 disk DVD edition from a few years back.And, as mentioned by others, the cover states incorrectly a running time of 161 minutes, when it is in fact 2:58h (178 minutes).", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[20, 23], :date=>" 2009 May 14", :title=>"Great Edition", :location=>"(San Francisco, CA USA)", :username=>"Christian Wolff", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/The-Good-Bad-Ugly-Collectors/product-reviews/B0001GF2DS"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"This is the best edition of GBU that I have seen so far. I do not agree with the reviewer that complained about the absence of grain due to DNR.", :clean_text=>"this is the best edition of gbu that i have seen so far i do not agree with the reviewer that complained about the absence of grain due to dnr.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"For me it looked sufficiently grainy and I could not see any DNR artifacts (on a 1080p plasma screen).", :clean_text=>"for me it looked sufficiently grainy and i could not see any dnr artifacts on a 1080p plasma screen).", :sentiment