ween good and bad became blurred, bringing on a decade of the anti-hero.", :clean_text=>"the line between good and bad became blurred bringing on a decade of the anti-hero.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>23, :text=>"This film still influences directors and writers throughout the world.", :clean_text=>"this film still influences directors and writers throughout the world.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>24, :text=>"It is a masterpiece of film making with a story that is epic.", :clean_text=>"it is a masterpiece of film making with a story that is epic.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>25, :text=>"Not only one of the greatest westerns ever made, one of the greatest films ever made.", :clean_text=>"not only one of the greatest westerns ever made one of the greatest films ever made.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:username=>"DreamExtractor", :useful=>"Super Reviewer", :date=>"June 25, 2011", :rating=>5, :percentage=>100.0, :content=>"The Good, The Bad, and The Ugly is the conclusion to the Man With No Name Trilogy, and is in my opinion the greatest western ever made (next to the 2010 True Grit).  The Good (Clint Eastwood), The Bad (Lee Van Cleef), and The Ugly (Eli Wallach) are three men, greedy and selfish men in the west during the time of American Civil War.  All three get caught in trying to find confederate gold, and will kill eachother for it.  The plot is much more than it sounds, its a journey through the west as we see the true violence, terror, beauty, hate, and sadness that the world was really like in that time, espically in the west.  Clint Eastwood is one of the most famous actors and directors in history, and we get to see him at his best in his golden days when he was a big rising star, and just having a star like him in this makes it feel even greater because we're not watching a old western film with some random actors, we're watching the king of westerns at his greatest.  Eli Wallach is amazing as well, he plays one of the cheatiest and stupididest people there is, and he fits the role to perfection.  Lee Van Cleef scared me as a kid, he played a ruthless bastard who was always one step ahead and he always played a great role with a straight face that made him one of the most remembered actors ever by being in this film.  The music in this film is its trademark, when people remember this film they sing the famous and amazingly made score that people remember to this day, and the rest of this music is tremendous as well.  The production of the film is great, they really tried hard to make this a spaghetti western.  There never was a moment that we are not supposed to watch because every moment is important to get the full feel of the film, and this is why The Good, The Bad, and The Ugly is the most famous western (and one of the most famous films) of all time.", :title=>nil, :location=>nil, :source=>{:vendor=>"rotten_tomatoes", :url=>"http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_good_the_bad_and_the_ugly"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"The Good, The Bad, and The Ugly is the conclusion to the Man With No Name Trilogy, and is in my opinion the greatest western ever made (next to the 2010 True Grit).", :clean_text=>"the good the bad and the ugly is the conclusion to the man with no name trilogy and is in my opinion the greatest western ever made next to the 2010 true grit).", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{:credibility=>80}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Clint Eastwood"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"The Good (Clint Eastwood), The Bad (Lee Van Cleef), and The Ugly (Eli Wallach) are three men, greedy and selfish men in the west during the time of American Civil War.", :clean_text=>"the good clint eastwood the bad lee van clee