.  It added to the films mood immensely.\r\rThis film obviously has inspired many modern filmmakers today (Rodriguez, Tarantino, among others) and I had to keep on reminding myself that this film was made in 1966.  I either thought it was made with today??s film techniques or some scenes were actually shot during the civil war time period.  It really took me back and followed it up with a great story.\r\rThe actors gave dialog in their native tongues and as a result there is a poor voice over synchronization throughout the movie.  I found this slightly distracting at times, but it did not deter me from enjoying the film and Sergio Leone??s great filmmaking brilliance shone through.  The sweeping panoramic shots were incredible and appealing throughout the film as well.\r \rAlthough I loved the characters Blondie - The Good, played by Clint Eastwood and Angel Eyes - The Bad, played by Lee Van Cleef; Tuco - The Ugly, played by Eli Wallach had an absolutely great performance and pushed the film to a greater level.\r\rI recommend this film to anyone, who loves movies and even remotely is interesting in the old west.", :title=>nil, :location=>nil, :source=>{:vendor=>"rotten_tomatoes", :url=>"http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_good_the_bad_and_the_ugly"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"I was battling weather to give this movie a 4  or 5, so I gave it the benefit of the doubt.", :clean_text=>"i was battling weather to give this movie a 4 or 5 so i gave it the benefit of the doubt.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"Once you get that high in my books, it?", :clean_text=>"once you get that high in my books it?", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>2, :text=>"?s pretty much the same.", :clean_text=>"?s pretty much the same.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>3, :te