gs=>["Brad Pitt"], :people_indexes=>[["Brad Pitt", [[53]]]]}]}, {:content=>"When I'm looking at the Top Ten list's of America's critics and the nominations of the DGA,WGA and all the other guilds and press associations, I terribly miss David Fincher's outstanding film \"Fight Club\",  which is possibly the best film of 1999.Not only is the film visualy  stunning, it is also very thought-provoking, wickedly funny and, above all,  extremely entertaining. Only few films managed to be so many things at  once. David Fincher, in my opinion one of the most exciting directors of  the decade, fills his movie with so many ideas that it would be sufficient  for three more movies, and they are not just gimmicks for their own sake,  they all mean something. Edward Norton and Brad Pitt are brilliant in the  leads and the soundtrack by the Dust Brothers fits perfectly to the  images.Many reviewers thought the film was fascist. I think you can only  call this ridiculous, since that assumes Fincher sympathizes with Tyler  Durden's project mayhem. In fact, he invites us to form our own opinion,  like Stanley Kubrick did in \"A Clockwork Orange\". \"Fight  Club\" hands over the resposibility  to the viewer. This may be  uncomfortable to some, others (like myself) will embrace this.", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[360, 406], :date=>" 2000 February 10", :title=>"The most underrated film of the last year", :location=>"(Frankfurt, Hessen)", :username=>"behet@stud.uni-frankfurt.de", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/Fight-Club-Two-Disc-Collectors-Edition/product-reviews/B00003W8NM"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"When I'm looking at the Top Ten list's of America's critics and the nominations of the DGA,WGA and all the other guilds and press associations, I terribly miss David Fincher's outstanding film \"Fight Club\",  which is possibly the best film of 1999.Not only is the film visualy  stunning, it is also very thought-provoking, wickedly funny and, above all,  extremely entertaining.", :clean_text=>"when i'm looking at the top ten list's of america's critics and the nominations of the dga,wga and all the other guilds and press associations i terribly miss david fincher's outstanding film fight club which is possibly the best film of 1999.not only is the film visualy stunning it is also very thought-provoking wickedly funny and above all extremely entertaining.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>3.0, :people_tags=>["David Fincher"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"Only few films managed to be so many things at  once.", :clean_text=>"only few films managed to be so many things at once.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>2, :text=>"David Fincher, in my opinion one of the most exciting directors of  the decade, fills his movie with so many ideas that it would be sufficient  for three more movies, and they are not just gimmicks for their own sake,  they all mean something.", :clean_text=>"david fincher in my opinion one of the most exciting directors of the decade fills his movie with so many ideas that it would be sufficient for three more movies and they are not just gimmicks for their own sake they all mean something.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["David Fincher"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>3, :text=>"Edward Norton and Brad Pitt are brilliant in the  leads and the soundtrack by the Dust Brothers fits perfectly to the  images.Many reviewers thought the film was fascist.", :clean_text=>"edward norton and brad pitt are brilliant in the leads and the soundtrack by the dust brothers fits perfectly to the images.many reviewers thought the film was fascist.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:sound=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Brad Pitt", "Edward Norton"], :people_indexes=>[["Brad Pitt", [[18]]], ["Edward Norton", [[0]]]]}, {:index=>4, :text=>"I think you can only  call this 