really fit to the end of the movie. Unfortunately Fight\nClub didn't have much success in Germany but anyway the movie got best\nreviews of the German press. I also have to mention the brilliance of Ed\nNorton and Brad Pitt who plays best in roles in which he performs the\nvillain. But it's quiet amazing what Edward Norton is able to do - he is\njust overwhelming. For that role he has to get the oscar.\n", :source=>{:vendor=>"imdb", :url=>"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0137523/"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"\n\nAfter watching this movie I was totally filled with enthusiasm.", :clean_text=>"after watching this movie i was totally filled with enthusiasm.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"Fight Club is definitly Fincher's best movie even better than se7en.", :clean_text=>"fight club is definitly fincher's best movie even better than se7en.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>2, :text=>"It's\nnot only the story but the optics which fascinated me. When I had seen it\nfor the second time I could see this movie with the knowledge of the\nconclusion which is really fascinating as you'll see Fight Club in a\ntotally\ndifferent perspective.", :clean_text=>"it's not only the story but the optics which fascinated me when i had seen it for the second time i could see this movie with the knowledge of the conclusion which is really fascinating as you'll see fight club in a totally different perspective.", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>3.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>3, :text=>"Also great about Fight Club is its soundtrack\nperformed by the Dust Brothers and especially the song 'Where is my mind'\nby\nthe Pixies which really fit to the end of the movie.", :clean_text=>"also great about fight club is its soundtrack performed by the dust brothers and especially the song where is my mind by the pixies which really fit to the end of the movie.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:sound=>100}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>4, :text=>"Unfortunately Fight\nClub didn't have much success in Germany but anyway the movie got best\nreviews of the German press.", :clean_text=>"unfortunately fight club didn't have much success in germany but anyway the movie got best reviews of the german press.", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>5, :text=>"I also have to mention the brilliance of Ed\nNorton and Brad Pitt who plays best in roles in which he performs the\nvillain.", :clean_text=>"i also have to mention the brilliance of ed norton and brad pitt who plays best in roles in which he performs the villain.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Brad Pitt"], :people_indexes=>[["Brad Pitt", [[55]]]]}, {:index=>6, :text=>"But it's quiet amazing what Edward Norton is able to do - he is\njust overwhelming.", :clean_text=>"but it's quiet amazing what edward norton is able to do he is just overwhelming.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Edward Norton"], :people_indexes=>[["Edward Norton", [[28]]]]}, {:index=>7, :text=>"For that role he has to get the oscar.\n", :clean_text=>"for that role he has to get the oscar", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{:cast=>70}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Edward Norton"], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:rating=>1.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[232, 372], :title=>"Generally positive comments", :username=>"Ian (rmic@home.com)", :location=>"from pittsburgh, pennsylvania", :date=>"15 February 2000", :content=>"\n\nThis film, is basically, at least in my opinion, one of the greatest films\never, period.  I read the book afterwards, and equally enjoyed the book.\nThe film is definitely for younger people, the critics of films, in general\nare older, so they cannot appreciate this film.  The film defines the\nyounger generation, only younger people can relate to it, however, older\npeople(middle aged+) can appreciate the art of the film, the beauty of the\ncamera work, as well as the excellent acting.  The film, in every aspect is\nfantastic, it begins with a rather humorous narration, from a person we grow\nto know as, \"narrator\".  It goes about to show how he lives, and his way of\nlife.  In these scenes alone, movie lines that will go down in history are\nsaid, and it's only the first twenty minutes.  The film tends to progress\nfaster and faster as the film continues.  We delve into the narrators\npsyche, and find that he is not unlike most people in this world, he has a\ntendency to say to people what they want to hear, even if it is not the\ntruth in it's entirety.  Almost all folks can relate to the main character,\nand he feels to be a real human, not a character in a story.  This, is\npartially due to the excellent directing, as well as book, but it is mostly\ndue to the fantastic performance by Edward Norton. It, in my opinion is an\nOscar performance.  Bradd Pitt gives his best performance to date, he is\ndefinitely an excellent coworker with David Fincher, they seem to share a\ncommon thread when it comes to film making I suppose.  I have full intention\nof purchasing this film when it is released on VHS and DVD.  Do yourself a\nfavour, see this film, if that is not an option, at least read the book.  If\nyou are younger and feel unrest with society, this is the film.\n\n", :source=>{:vendor=>"imdb", :url=>"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0137523/"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"\n\nThis film, is basically, at least in my opinion, one of the greatest films\never, period.", :clean_text=>"this film is basically at least in my opinion one of the greatest films ever period.", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"I read the book afterwards, and equally enjoyed 