ansfer includes a 1080p resolution and a 1.85:1 aspect ratio that matches the original.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:novelty=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>9, :text=>"Spielberg personally supervised the high definition transfer and the lossless audio (DTS-HD Master Audio 5.1) restoration of the film from the 35mm film original negative.", :clean_text=>"spielberg personally supervised the high definition transfer and the lossless audio dts-hd master audio 5.1 restoration of the film from the 35mm film original negative.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:sound=>50, :novelty=>50}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>10, :text=>"Special features include:Voices from the List: Documentary featuring a number of testimonies and stories from men and women who survived the Holocaust thanks to Oskar Schindler.USC Shoah Foundation Story with Steven Spielberg", :clean_text=>"special features include:voices from the list documentary featuring a number of testimonies and stories from men and women who survived the holocaust thanks to oskar schindler.usc shoah foundation story with steven spielberg", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Liam Neeson", "Steven Spielberg"], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"Meet Oskar Schindler. A German living in occupied Poland during World War II. A member in good standing of the Nazi party. A womanizer, a war profiteer...and ultimately a man of conscience. A man who became one of the great unsung heroes and humanitarians of the war.\"Schindler's List\" chronicles Oskar Schindler's spiritual odyssey from war profiteer to humanitarian and hero.  Winner of seven Academy Awards in 1993, including Best Picture, this  harrowing and heart-rending film is Steven Spielberg's masterpiece, and perhaps one of the finest and most important movies ever made.  It depicts Schindler's ultimately successful attempt to rescue 1,100 Jews from Hitler's \"Final Solution\" by getting them to safety outside Poland.Dynamic performances abound in this beautiful movie,  Especially noteworthy are Liam Neeson as the suave Schindler, Ralph Fiennes as the monstrously depraved Nazi colonel, Amon Goeth, and Ben Kingsley as the dignified, principled Jewish prisoner Itzhak Stern.\"Schindler's List\" is definitely not light entertainment!  This beautiful movie allows viewers to feel like they're actually a part of one of the darkest, most horrific periods in history. (I'm sure this is the reason the film was shot in black-and-white, with only minor \"colorized\" bits included.)  The story of the Holocaust needs to be told over and over again, in hopes  that future generations can understand the horrors perpetrated on an entire race of people and prevent future occurrences.  \"Schindler's List\" is perhaps one of the best and most effective vehicles for telling that story I've ever experienced.", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[253, 291], :date=>" 2001 February 21", :title=>"A cinematic masterpiece!", :location=>"(Woolwich, ME USA)", :username=>"Mike Powers \"mkp51\"", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/Schindlers-List-Blu-ray-DIGITAL-UltraViolet/product-reviews/B00B0U2SEA"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"Meet Oskar Schindler.", :clean_text=>"meet oskar schindler.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Liam Neeson"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"A German living in occupied Poland during World War II.", :clean_text=>"a german living in occupied poland during world war ii.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>2, :text=>"A member in good standing of the Nazi party.", :clean_text=>"a member in good standing of the nazi party.", :sentiment=>1, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>3, :text=>"A womanizer, a war profiteer...and ultimately a man 