bound in this beautiful movie especially noteworthy are liam neeson as the suave schindler ralph fiennes as the monstrously depraved nazi colonel amon goeth and ben kingsley as the dignified principled jewish prisoner itzhak stern.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:vision=>20}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Liam Neeson", "Ben Kingsley", "Ralph Fiennes"], :people_indexes=>[["Liam Neeson", [[226]]], ["Ben Kingsley", [[323]]], ["Ralph Fiennes", [[251]]]]}, {:index=>8, :text=>"\"Schindler's List\" is definitely not light entertainment!", :clean_text=>"\"schindler's list is definitely not light entertainment!", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>9, :text=>"This beautiful movie allows viewers to feel like they're actually a part of one of the darkest, most horrific periods in history.", :clean_text=>"this beautiful movie allows viewers to feel like they're actually a part of one of the darkest most horrific periods in history.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:vision=>20}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>10, :text=>"(I'm sure this is the reason the film was shot in black-and-white, with only minor \"colorized\" bits included.", :clean_text=>"(i'm sure this is the reason the film was shot in black-and-white with only minor colorized bits included.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:cinematography=>80}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>11, :text=>")  The story of the Holocaust needs to be told over and over again, in hopes  that future generations can understand the horrors perpetrated on an entire race of people and prevent future occurrences.", :clean_text=>"the story of the holocaust needs to be told over and over again in hopes that future generations can understand the horrors perpetrated on an entire race of people and prevent future occurrences.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>12, :text=>"\"Schindler's List\" is perhaps one of the best and most effective vehicles for telling that story I've ever experienced.", :clean_text=>"\"schindler's list is perhaps one of the best and most effective vehicles for telling that story i've ever experienced.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"Any way you stack it, Steven Spielberg's 1993 masterpiece SCHINDLER'S LIST is one of the most important and enlightening films ever made. It is a heartfelt, deeply personal film about one of the ghastliest events in human history--the Holocaust--and how one man, a Nazi profiteer by the name of Oskar Schindler, while motivated by money, managed to save some 1200 Jews from the gas chambers of Auschwitz during World War II.Spielberg wisely does not gloss over the fact that Schindler was every bit the womanizer as he was an astute, cagey businessman who made deals with the Nazis to set up an enamelware factory in the Cracow ghetto and employ the Jewish populace there. But his very trusted secretary Itzhak Stern (Ben Kingsley) manages to awaken a latent spark of humanity in the once cold-blooded Schindler. By the time the war is over and the facts are known about the Nazi atrocities, Schindler is financially broke but spiritually enriched. \"He who saves one life saves the world entire.\"Filmed in somber, documentary-like black-and-white by Janusz Kaminski, SCHINDLER'S LIST features superb performances by Neeson and Kingsley, as well as British actor Ralph Fiennes as the extraordinarily chilling Nazi commandant Amon Goeth, whose basic senses of Nazi business Schindler must appeal to while keeping the fact that he is sheltering the Jews a secret. Spielberg spares nothing in showing us the horrors of the Nazis barbarism; and although it is, not surprisingly, a very lengthy film (three hours and ten minutes), a lot happens for us to absorb, so it never becomes ponderous or heavy-handed.Winner of seven Oscars, including a Best Director nod to Spielberg that was long overdue, SCHINDLER'S LIST shows us the worst in humanity, but also the best as well. Even in so much pain and death, there is hope. And that is why this film is such a masterpiece.", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[130, 152], :date=>" 2002 June 5", :title=>"The List Is A Life", :location=>"(San Gabriel, CA USA)", :username=>"Erik North", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/Schindlers-List-Blu-ray-DIGITAL-UltraViolet/product-reviews/B00B0U2SEA"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"Any way you stack it, Steven Spielberg's 1993 masterpiece SCHINDLER'S LIST is one of the most important and enlightening films ever made.", :clean_text=>"any way you stack it steven spielberg's 1993 masterpiece schindler's list is one of the most important and enlightening films ever made.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>["Steven Spielberg"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"It is a heartfelt, deeply personal film about one of the ghastliest events in human history--the Holocaust--and how one man, a Nazi profiteer by the name of Oskar Schindler, while motivated by money, managed to save some 1200 Jews from the gas chambers of Auschwitz during World War II.Spielberg wisely does not gloss over the fact that Schindler was every bit the womanizer as he was an astute, cagey businessman who made deals with the Nazis to set up an enamelware factory in the Cracow ghetto and employ the Jewish populace there.", :clean_text=>"it is a heartfelt deeply personal film about one of the ghastliest events in human history--the holocaust--and how one man a nazi profiteer by the name of oskar schindler while motivated by money managed to save some 1200 jews from the gas chambers of auschwitz during world war ii.spielberg wisely does not gloss over the fact that schindler was every bit the womanizer as he was an astute cagey businessman who made 