isoners for breakfast.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>25, :cinematography=>10}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ralph Fiennes"], :people_indexes=>[["Ralph Fiennes", [[196]]]]}, {:index=>14, :text=>"On the other hand, \"Schindler's List\" contains a great many images that look like they were etched on mirrors, such as the famous shot of a little boy hiding from the Nazis at the bottom of a latrine.", :clean_text=>"on the other hand schindler's list contains a great many images that look like they were etched on mirrors such as the famous shot of a little boy hiding from the nazis at the bottom of a latrine.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:cinematography=>80}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>15, :text=>"At those moments, even when (as one character says) \"all around lies the gulf,\" the pictures soak up a truly heavenly light, as though Someone were watching.The performers involved certainly behave as though Someone were watching, and they turn in the work of their lives, from the stars to the bit players.", :clean_text=>"at those moments even when as one character says all around lies the gulf the pictures soak up a truly heavenly light as though someone were watching.the performers involved certainly behave as though someone were watching and they turn in the work of their lives from the stars to the bit players.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:plot=>50}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>16, :text=>"Neeson has just the right sort of big, craggy face that can show decadence one minute and agony the next, and he's got the talent to run the whole gamut in all the right places.", :clean_text=>"neeson has just the right sort of big craggy face that can show decadence one minute and agony the next and he's got the talent to run the whole gamut in all the right places.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>17, :text=>"Fiennes, in his first major role, resembles nothing so much as a sort of human hog, but a cunning and crazed one - he seems able to sweat on cue.  Ben Kingsley as Schindler's factory manager, with almost no change in his facial expression, makes us see how he moves from suspicion to hope to love for this strange animal, his boss.", :clean_text=>"fiennes in his first major role resembles nothing so much as a sort of human hog but a cunning and crazed one he seems able to sweat on cue ben kingsley as schindler's factory manager with almost no change in his facial expression makes us see how he moves from suspicion to hope to love for this strange animal his boss.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:cast=>70}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ben Kingsley"], :people_indexes=>[["Ben Kingsley", [[147]]]]}, {:index=>18, :text=>"And besides these monumental performances, there's the black marketeer who finagles his customers with one breath and loves his wife with the next; the engineer who sacrifices her life to the fact that concrete needs to be poured with care; the old hinge-maker who waits on his knees for a miracle involving a jammed gun; the pretty young woman who informs Schindler that he's running a haven rather than a factory; the kindly but finally gutless industrialist, and a many dozen others, all unforgettable.And then there's Spielberg's damping down his usual sentimentality, his choice of Yiddish music for the soundtrack, his placement of the camera at a quiet and unobtrusive angle for the worst of evils - I found all of this pretty nearly perfect, but there were those who complained about the movie's historical inaccuracy.", :clean_text=>"and besides these monumental performances there's the black marketeer who finagles his customers with one breath and loves his wife with the next the engineer who sacrifices her life to the fact that concrete needs to be poured with care the old hinge-maker who waits on his knees for a miracle involving a jammed gun the pretty young woman who informs schindler that he's running a haven rather than a factory the kindly but finally gutless industrialist and a many dozen others all unforgettable.and then there's spielberg's damping down his usual sentimentality his choice of yiddish music for the soundtrack his placement of the camera at a quiet and unobtrusive angle for the worst of evils i found all of this pretty nearly perfect but there were those who complained about the movie's historical inaccuracy.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{:sound=>200}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Ben Kingsley"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>19, :text=>"In one scene, much noted for its supposed softening of the facts, Schindler's female \"employees\" find themselves in a big room with shower heads in the ceiling and actually get a shower instead of a flood of poison gas.", :clean_text=>"in one scene much noted for its supposed softening of the facts schindler's female employees find themselves in a big room with shower heads in the ceiling and actually get a shower instead of a flood of poison gas.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{:cinematography=>80}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>20, :text=>"It's true that most prisoners were not so fortunate, and that such scenes may play into the hands of the filth who claim that there was no cyanide in the camps, but I can't see that as an argument against this movie.", :clean_text=>"it's true that most prisoners were not so fortunate and that such scenes may play into the hands of the filth who claim that there was no cyanide in the camps but i can't see that as an argument against this movie.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{:credibility=>80}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>21, :text=>"If nothing else, the looks of tension on the women's faces before the water comes down is more than enough to tell us what they expect to get.After all, Spielberg is not a documentarian, he's a storyteller; this story could not have had a better servant.", :clean_text=>"if nothing else the looks of tension on the women's faces before the water comes down is more than enough to tell us what they expect to get.after all spielberg is not a documentarian he's a storyteller this story could not have had a better servant.", :sentiment=>-1, :context_tags=>{:plot=>100}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>22, :text=>"The meaning of the Holocaust is as plain as plain here, particularly at the end when Schindler realizes that he could have saved a few more human beings if he had just thought to sell his car or his gold Nazi pin.", :clean_text=>"the meaning of the holocaust is as plain as plain here particularly at the end when schindler realizes that he could have saved a few more human beings if he had just thought to sell his car or his gold nazi pin.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>23, :text=>"He crumples weeping to his knees, only to be lifted up by the men and women he has saved.A little later we learn that the descendants of Schindler's Jews living in Israel outnumber the entire current Jewish population of Poland.", :clean_text=>"he crumples weeping to his knees only to be lifted up by the men and women he has saved.a little later we learn that the descendants of schindler's jews living in israel outnumber the entire current jewish population of poland.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>24, :text=>"That silences all criticism, as the movie audience already knew.", :clean_text=>"that silences all criticism as the movie audience already knew.", :sentiment=>-2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>25, :text=>"Hence the quiet after the final credits.Benshlomo says nothing.", :clean_text=>"hence the quiet after the final credits.benshlomo says nothing.", :sentiment=>0, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"Wow.  Just wow.  That's all.  Gripping, moving, tear jerking, uplifting, top notch acting, stunning photography, script line in synch with the book, true life ending, OMG.  This is the story of Oskar Schindler who kept over 1,000 people alive during the Nazi reign.  This is a movie (and book) you must watch (or read) to believe.  I generally do not care for \"war\" movies, and although I love splatter films and gory fiction books, I despise real life violence.  Having once been a victim of violent crime, I have a relationship with real life horror that I do not like to explore, but the heroism of this story so dramatically overwhelms the real horrors that it is a must see for anyone.  Liam Neeson is phenomenal in his role as Schindler, and Ben Kingsley along with Ralph Finnes fills out the superb acting.  Difficult to watch, impossible to forget, it is truly the story of heroism on its grandest scale.The most poignant moment is the one, the only, faded splash of faint color in the little girls red coat; the rest of the movie is black and white, which only adds to the impact of the total emotion of this fantastic film.", :rating=>5.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[16, 17], :date=>" 2003 August 14", :title=>"Horrible subject brought beautifully to film", :location=>"(Washington State)", :username=>"Schtinky \"Schtinky\"", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/Schindlers-List-Blu-ray-DIGITAL-UltraViolet/product-reviews/B00B0U2SEA"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"Wow.  Just wow.", :clean_text=>"wow just wow.", :sentiment=>2, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"That's all.  Gripping, moving, tear jerking, uplifting, top notch acting, stunning photography, script line in synch with the book, true life ending, OMG.", :clean_text=>"that's all gripping moving tear jerking uplifting top notch acting stunning photogr